The paper deals with the automaticity of linear orderings, which is a topic in logic and theoretical computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which specifically deals with logical aspects of computer science. The paper also involves formal languages and automata, which are topics covered in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of finite automata suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which deals with the study of the resources required to solve computational problems. Finally, the paper involves trees, which are a common data structure in computer science, and thus could also be classified under cs.LT (Logic and Type Theory).
